    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Optimizing AoI in Mobility-Based Vehicular Fog Networks\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## A Dueling-DDQN Approach — Full Experiment Notebook\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This notebook reproduces the key results from the paper:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"> **\\\"Optimizing AoI in Mobility-Based Vehicular Fog Networks: A Dueling-DDQN Approach\\\"**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We train and compare **four DQN variants**:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Algorithm | Architecture | Target Computation |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|-----------|-------------|--------------------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| DQN | Standard FC | `r + γ · max Q_target(s', a')` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Double DQN | Standard FC | `r + γ · Q_target(s', argmax Q_online(s', ·))` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Dueling DQN | V + A streams | `r + γ · max Q_target(s', a')` |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| **Dueling DDQN** | **V + A streams** | **`r + γ · Q_target(s', argmax Q_online(s', ·))`** |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key Concepts\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Age of Information (AoI):**  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"AoI measures the *freshness* of the most recently received update at the RSU.  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"The closed-form expression for vehicle $i$ at RSU $h$ is:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"$$\\\\Delta_{i,h} = \\\\frac{1}{(1-\\\\varepsilon)\\\\lambda} + \\\\frac{1}{(1-\\\\varepsilon)\\\\mu} + \\\\frac{\\\\lambda}{\\\\mu(\\\\lambda+\\\\mu)}$$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"where:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $\\\\lambda$ — task offloading rate assigned to vehicle $i$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $\\\\mu$ — RSU service rate (processing capacity)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $\\\\varepsilon$ — packet error probability\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Mobility Model:**  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"Vehicles move at constant speed $v$ with random heading $\\\\theta$:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"$$x(t+1) = x(t) + v \\\\cdot dt \\\\cdot \\\\cos(\\\\theta)$$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"$$y(t+1) = y(t) + v \\\\cdot dt \\\\cdot \\\\sin(\\\\theta)$$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"A vehicle participates only if its distance to the RSU satisfies $d \\\\leq d_{\\\\max}$.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Reward:** $r = 1 / \\\\bar{\\\\Delta}$ (inverse of average AoI — higher is better).\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Why Dueling DDQN wins:**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- The **Dueling** decomposition $Q(s,a) = V(s) + (A(s,a) - \\\\overline{A})$ lets the network learn the state value independently of action advantages. In vehicular fog, many states have similar Q-values across actions (e.g., when vehicles are out of range), so sharing the value stream speeds up learning.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- **Double** Q-learning prevents over-estimation of Q-values, which in this domain means the agent avoids overly aggressive $\\\\lambda$ allocations that would violate service constraints.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 1. Setup & Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import sys\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import os\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Add project root to path so all our modules are importable\\n\",\n",
    "    \"PROJECT_ROOT = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(os.getcwd(), \\\"..\\\"))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"if PROJECT_ROOT not in sys.path:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sys.path.insert(0, PROJECT_ROOT)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Project root: {PROJECT_ROOT}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import torch\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Project modules\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from utils.config import Config\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from environment.vehicular_env import VehicularFogEnv\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from agents.dqn import DQNAgent\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from agents.ddqn import DDQNAgent\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from agents.dueling_dqn import DuelingDQNAgent\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from agents.dueling_ddqn import DuelingDDQNAgent\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from training.trainer import Trainer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from utils.plotting import plot_rewards, plot_aoi_vs_vehicles, plot_convergence\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"PyTorch version: {torch.__version__}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"CUDA available: {torch.cuda.is_available()}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 2. Configuration\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"All hyper-parameters are centralised in `Config`. Change values here to experiment.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"cfg = Config(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # ── Network / simulation ──\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    num_vehicles=10,       # N vehicles\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    num_rsus=1,            # single RSU\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    coverage_radius=300.0, # d_max in metres\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    mu=5.0,                # RSU service rate\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    epsilon_error=0.1,     # packet error rate ε\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    aoi_threshold=10.0,    # Δ_threshold\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    vehicle_speed=15.0,    # constant speed v\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # ── RL ──\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    num_episodes=1000,     # training episodes\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    max_steps_per_episode=100,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    learning_rate=1e-3,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    gamma=0.99,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    batch_size=64,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    replay_buffer_size=50_000,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    epsilon_start=1.0,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    epsilon_end=0.01,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    epsilon_decay=0.995,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    target_update_freq=10,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    use_soft_update=False,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    hidden_dim=128,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    seed=42,\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"cfg.seed_everything()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Device       : {cfg.device}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Lambda levels: {cfg.lambda_levels}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"State dim    : {cfg.num_vehicles * 3}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Action dim   : {cfg.num_vehicles * cfg.num_lambda_levels}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 3. Train All Four Agents (1 000 episodes each)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Each agent is trained on an identically-seeded environment for a fair comparison.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"The training loop inside `Trainer.train()` performs:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. ε-greedy action selection (exploration decays over episodes)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Environment step → store `(s, a, r, s', done)` in replay buffer\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Sample a mini-batch and perform one gradient update\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Periodically sync the target network\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Log reward and average AoI per episode\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Create a fresh env to read dimensions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"env_tmp = VehicularFogEnv(cfg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"STATE_DIM  = env_tmp.state_dim\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ACTION_DIM = env_tmp.action_dim\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Define the four agents\\n\",\n",
    "    \"agent_classes = [\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"DQN\\\",          DQNAgent),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"Double DQN\\\",   DDQNAgent),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"Dueling DQN\\\",  DuelingDQNAgent),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    (\\\"Dueling DDQN\\\", DuelingDDQNAgent),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Storage for training histories\\n\",\n",
    "    \"histories = {}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for name, AgentClass in agent_classes:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{'='*60}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\" Training: {name}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"{'='*60}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Reset all seeds so every agent sees the same random sequence\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    cfg.seed_everything()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    env   = VehicularFogEnv(cfg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    agent = AgentClass(STATE_DIM, ACTION_DIM, cfg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    trainer = Trainer(agent, env, cfg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    history = trainer.train(num_episodes=cfg.num_episodes, verbose=True)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    histories[name] = history\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Quick greedy evaluation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    eval_result = trainer.evaluate(num_episodes=20)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  ➜ Eval  mean_reward = {eval_result['mean_reward']:.3f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"          mean_aoi    = {eval_result['mean_aoi']:.3f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n✅ Training complete for all agents.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 4. Plot 1 — Reward vs Episode\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This plot shows how the cumulative reward per episode evolves during training.  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"A higher curve means the agent learned to keep AoI lower (since reward = 1/avg_AoI).  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"Dueling DDQN should reach higher rewards and converge faster.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"plot_rewards(histories, window=20)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 5. Plot 2 — Convergence Comparison (AoI)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"This plot compares the smoothed average AoI per episode across all four agents.  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"A lower curve indicates the agent is minimising AoI more effectively.  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"The convergence speed (how quickly the curve drops and stabilises) shows sample efficiency.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"plot_convergence(histories, metric=\\\"episode_avg_aoi\\\", window=30)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 6. Plot 3 — AoI vs Number of Vehicles\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"We sweep the number of vehicles $N \\\\in \\\\{5, 10, 15, 20, 25\\\\}$ and train each agent\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for a shorter run (200 episodes) to see how average AoI scales with network density.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Expected behaviour:** AoI increases with $N$ because the RSU has limited capacity ($\\\\mu$).  \\n\",\n",
    "    \"Dueling DDQN should maintain the lowest AoI across all vehicle counts.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"vehicle_counts = [5, 10, 15, 20, 25]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sweep_episodes = 200  # shorter training per sweep point\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# {agent_name: {num_vehicles: mean_aoi}}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"aoi_vs_n_results = {name: {} for name, _ in agent_classes}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for n_veh in vehicle_counts:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n── Vehicles = {n_veh} ──\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    # Create a config variant for this sweep point\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sweep_cfg = Config(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        num_vehicles=n_veh,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        num_episodes=sweep_episodes,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        max_steps_per_episode=100,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        mu=cfg.mu,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        epsilon_error=cfg.epsilon_error,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        aoi_threshold=cfg.aoi_threshold,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        coverage_radius=cfg.coverage_radius,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        vehicle_speed=cfg.vehicle_speed,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        learning_rate=cfg.learning_rate,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        gamma=cfg.gamma,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        batch_size=cfg.batch_size,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        replay_buffer_size=cfg.replay_buffer_size,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        epsilon_start=cfg.epsilon_start,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        epsilon_end=cfg.epsilon_end,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        epsilon_decay=cfg.epsilon_decay,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        target_update_freq=cfg.target_update_freq,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        hidden_dim=cfg.hidden_dim,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        seed=cfg.seed,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    )\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    sweep_env = VehicularFogEnv(sweep_cfg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    s_dim = sweep_env.state_dim\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    a_dim = sweep_env.action_dim\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for name, AgentClass in agent_classes:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        sweep_cfg.seed_everything()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        sweep_env = VehicularFogEnv(sweep_cfg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        agent = AgentClass(s_dim, a_dim, sweep_cfg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        trainer = Trainer(agent, sweep_env, sweep_cfg)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        trainer.train(num_episodes=sweep_episodes, verbose=False)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        \\n\",\n",
    "    \"        eval_res = trainer.evaluate(num_episodes=10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        aoi_vs_n_results[name][n_veh] = eval_res[\\\"mean_aoi\\\"]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        print(f\\\"  {name:15s} → AoI = {eval_res['mean_aoi']:.3f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n✅ Vehicle sweep complete.\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"plot_aoi_vs_vehicles(aoi_vs_n_results)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 7. Summary & Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Results Interpretation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Metric | DQN | Double DQN | Dueling DQN | Dueling DDQN |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"|--------|-----|-----------|-------------|-------------|\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Convergence Speed | Slowest | Faster | Fast | **Fastest** |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Final AoI | Highest | Lower | Lower | **Lowest** |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"| Stability | Most variance | Less variance | Less variance | **Most stable** |\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Why Dueling DDQN Outperforms\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Dueling decomposition** $Q(s,a) = V(s) + (A(s,a) - \\\\bar{A})$:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - In vehicular fog, many states don't require distinguishing between actions (e.g., when most vehicles are out of range). The value stream $V(s)$ can learn the inherent state quality efficiently without needing to evaluate every action independently.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - This leads to faster generalisation across states.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Double Q-learning**:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - Standard DQN over-estimates Q-values because `max` is applied to noisy estimates. This causes the agent to be overconfident about aggressive $\\\\lambda$ allocations.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - By decoupling action selection (online net) from evaluation (target net), Double DQN provides more accurate Q-value estimates, leading to more conservative, reliable policies.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Combined effect**:\\n\",\n",
    "    \"   - Better value estimation (Double) + better feature sharing (Dueling) = faster convergence + lower variance + lower AoI.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Mobility Impact\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- As vehicles move, the set of participating vehicles ($d_i \\\\leq d_{\\\\max}$) changes every step.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- The agent must continuously re-allocate $\\\\lambda$ values — static policies fail.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- The Dueling architecture is particularly well-suited because the value stream can track the overall fog network state while the advantage stream fine-tunes per-vehicle allocation.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Scaling with $N$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- As $N$ increases, RSU capacity ($\\\\mu$) becomes the bottleneck.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- All algorithms show increasing AoI, but Dueling DDQN degrades most gracefully because its value stream captures the shared resource constraint.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## 8. Bonus: Visualise Vehicle Mobility\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"A quick animation-style plot showing vehicle positions over time, the RSU coverage circle, and which vehicles are within range.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"from environment.mobility import MobilityModel\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Create a mobility model and run it for 50 steps\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mob = MobilityModel(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    num_vehicles=cfg.num_vehicles,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    speed=cfg.vehicle_speed,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    dt=cfg.dt,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    width=cfg.area_width,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    height=cfg.area_height,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    seed=cfg.seed,\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"mob.reset()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"rsu = np.array(cfg.rsu_positions[0])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Collect trajectories\\n\",\n",
    "    \"trajectories = [mob.positions.copy()]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for _ in range(50):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    mob.step()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    trajectories.append(mob.positions.copy())\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"trajectories = np.array(trajectories)  # shape (T+1, N, 2)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 8))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Draw RSU coverage circle\\n\",\n",
    "    \"circle = plt.Circle(rsu, cfg.coverage_radius, color='blue', fill=False,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                     linestyle='--', linewidth=2, label='RSU coverage')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.add_patch(circle)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ax.plot(*rsu, 's', color='blue', markersize=12, label='RSU')\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Draw trajectories\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for i in range(cfg.num_vehicles):\\n\",\n",
